Section Information: Selected Topics in CS- Internet of Things (IoT) Security The Internet of Things (IoT) brings new security challenges beyond those faced in the Internet of Computer (IoC), including due to scale (number of devices) and resource constraints. This course examines systems security issues that arise, and the security and privacy challenges as we embed computational and communications capabilities into a vast array of physical objects. Priority will be given to the students in the OCICS joint institute and the students in the Thesis based research programs.
